Nissan Motor Said to Hire Banks for Bond Investor Meetings

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-09-16T03:14:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/nissan-motor-said-to-hire-banks-for-bond-investor-meetings-1-.html
Nissan Motor  Co. hired banks to
arrange a series of meetings with bond investors in Hong Kong
and Singapore, according to a person familiar with the matter.  HSBC Holdings Plc and Standard Chartered Plc are arranging
the offshore yuan fixed-income meetings, said the person, who
asked not to be identified because the details are private.  Three calls each to Mitsuru Yonekawa and Toshitake
Inoshita, spokesmen at Nissan Motor, were unanswered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bloomberg News in Beijing at 
 hsanderson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shelley Smith at 
 ssmith118@bloomberg.net  